      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOCHINVAR JAG (2) is flying having completed a winning hat trick by leading from this barrier for a 1.7m success at Newcastle last time. Led from the outside barrier to score at Menangle prior. Can push forward again from this draw and drops to a distance where his record is strong. MCLEAN (4) was good from wider in a higher-graded race last start, racing parked but boxing on to be beaten less than 3 metres into fourth. Won twice in a row at this circuit and distance prior. Big chance. NOSAER (8) has been tackling stronger company of late. Draws wide but came from the back row to win in a similar class three back at Penrith so is better placed. HUNTER SHANNON (6) draws deeper but was good last time out when third behind Group performer Ripp.",
